ext{i}})$ is unitary, but does not satisfy the\nmore general identity\n$U_{\\text{ph}}(t_{3},t_{2})U_{\\text{ph}}(t_{2},t_{1})=U_{\\text{ph}}(t_{3},t_{1})$.\nAs a consequence, $U_{\\text{ph}}(t_{\\text{f}},t_{\\text{i}})$ cannot be derived\nfrom a Hamiltonian in a standard way, in the presence of purely virtual\nparticles.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 15 Apr 2023 22:08:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-18"}
