pans that could be the seeds for the $h<0$\nvortex sheets that form in the lower half of the trefoil as the\n$\\sqrt{\\nu}Z(t)$ phase begins and can explain accelerated growth of the\nenstrophy and evidence for finite-time energy dissipation $\\Delta E_\\epsilon$.\nDespite the initial symmetries.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 16 Apr 2023 05:02:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-18"}
